  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Sorry guys, I'm late on that.\n\nI really think it's not a good idea to expose the `facetRefinements` and `disjunctiveRefinements` in the `searchParameters` options. Those are super internal values of the underlying AlgoliaSearch Helper and it's way too confusing for our users to deal with them mixed with the actual search parameters. (I'm not even speaking about hierarchical refinements & numerical refinements.)\n\nThe simple way to add initial refinements is to build a custom widget:\n\n``` javascript\n      var search = instantsearch({\n        appId: 'YourApplicationID',\n        apiKey: 'YourSearchOnlyAPIKey',\n        indexName: 'YourIndexName'\n      });\n\n      search.addWidget({\n        init: function(args) {\n          args.helper. addFacetRefinement('category', 'phone');\n        }\n      });\n```\n\nIt's documented, I don't need to think about internal naming & I can manipulate the state super easily.\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
    "created_at": "2016-05-24T11:39:46Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/1027#issuecomment-221243226",
    "id": 221243226,
